<p>Everyone: 2721 is not a kinch self-insert. It isn't. Yes, Lyris is a death satellite that discovered how to be integrated into humanity as a trans woman Tumblr user. That does not make Lyris kinch.</p>
<p>Kinch, like everyone else here, is a writer. That means she's writing characters that are different from herself. It's that someone sees, &quot;Oh, that character is a Tumblrina. It must be a self-insert.&quot; Really, that statement really shows a shallowness in thought. Why can't someone write a character that has real-world analogues that isn't immediately branded a self-insert?</p>
<p>You can argue that every character has pieces of themselves in it, and sure, it's true, they're all creations from our minds, they're all informed by our experiences, but that's only one portion of the character creation process.</p>
<p>The fact remains: Lyris is not a kinch self-insert. A lot of people just desperately, desperately <em>want</em> Lyris to be a self-insert.</p>

